## React Component Structure

### File Naming
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Place components in `src/components/` directory
- Component files named after their primary export: `UserCard.jsx`, `LoginForm.tsx`

### Component Patterns
```javascript
// Functional component with TypeScript
import React from 'react';

interface UserCardProps {
  user: {
    name: string;
    email: string;
  };
  onClick?: () => void;
}

const UserCard: React.FC<UserCardProps> = ({ user, onClick }) => {
  return (
    <div className="user-card" onClick={onClick}>
      <h3>{user.name}</h3>
      <p>{user.email}</p>
    </div>
  );
};

export default UserCard;
```

## Styling Conventions

### CSS/Styled Components
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling when available (v4+)
- Implement consistent class naming: `bg-primary`, `text-secondary`
- Use utility-first approach with consistent spacing system
- Avoid inline styles

### Component Structure
- Keep components small and focused
- Prefer composition over inheritance  
- Use props for customization
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces

## Best Practices

### State Management
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext)
- Keep component state minimal
- Separate business logic from UI rendering

### Performance
- Memoize expensive calculations with useMemo
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders with useCallback
- Lazy load components when appropriate
- Use React.memo for pure components

### Accessibility
- Add proper ARIA attributes where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation support
- Provide meaningful alt text for images
- Maintain sufficient color contrast

### Production Reliability
- All component configuration parameters should be validated
- Feature flags should be used for experimental or risky component changes
- Performance metrics should be monitored for component rendering
- Components should handle error boundaries gracefully